<% content_for :page_title do %><h2>Human Kennels</h2><% end %>
	
<div class="sidebox slim right">
  <div class="box slim">
    <h4>Human Slaves</h4>
    <p class="em">Enslaved humans have had their spirit broken and no longer serve as companions and confer no bonuses. 
	Instead they spend their hours devoting to searching for Kibble to bring to their master.</p>
	<p>Your pet has <strong><%= pluralize(@slave_count, 'slave') %></strong> working for them.</p>
	<p>
	  <% if @slave_count > 0 %>
	    Your pet's slaves are earning Â±<strong id='slave-earnings'><%= current_user_pet.slave_earnings %></strong> Kibble/day.
	  <% end %>
	</p>
  </div>

  <div class="box slim">
    <h4>Human Activity</h4>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="box">
  <h3>Domesticated Human Companions</h3>
  <p class="em">Humans are useful, if stupid. Domesticated humans can confer a variety of bonuses and skills, but they're 
	violent and irrational creatures who must be continually appeased and coddled or they'll turn to infighting and kill 
	each other. The higher your pet's Affection, the more humans they can keep and the happier the humans will be.</p>
  
  <table class="kennels">
	<tbody>
	<% @tames.each do |tame| %>
	<tr>
	  <table class='domesticated-human'>
		<tbody>
		<tr><th colspan="3"><%= tame.human.name %></th></tr>
		<tr>
		  <td><%= avatar_image(tame.human, 'medium') %></td>
		  <td>
			<div>Type: <strong><%= tame.human.human_type %></strong></div>
			<div>Power: <strong><%= tame.human.power %></strong></div>
			<div>Required Level: <strong><%= tame.human.required_rank %></strong></div>
			<div>Rarity: <strong><%= tame.human.difficulty %></strong></div>
		  </td>
		  <td class="em" colspan="2"><%= tame.human.description %></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		  <td>
		    <strong><%= facebook_link_to "Enslave", enslave_facebook_kennel_path(tame.id) %></strong>
			<br />
		    <strong><%= facebook_link_to "Release", release_facebook_kennel_path(tame.id) %></strong>
		  </td>
		</tr>
		</tbody>
	  </table>
	</tr>
	<% end %>
	</tbody>
  </table>
</div>